  "body": "Hi, \r\nI'm using `\"hardhat\": \"2.12.4\"` and `\"@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox\": \"2.0.0\"`\r\n\r\nI've encountered this problem, when trying to deploy some contracts to hardhat local node via script. \r\nThe error stack was:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    const error = new ProviderError(\"HttpProviderError\", -1);\r\n                  ^\r\nProviderError: HttpProviderError\r\n    at HttpProvider.request (D:\\***\\node_modules\\hardhat\\src\\internal\\core\\providers\\http.ts:78:19)\r\n    at AutomaticSenderProvider.request .....\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter couple of hours of debugging and version changing I've just added:\r\n`console.log(response)` after `isErrorReponse()` checks in `node_modules/hardhat/internal/core/providers/http.js` and found out that the errors were actually not hardhat internal but my own, inside deploy script (related to contract logic). \r\nBut this was so unclear...\r\n\r\nPlease, add some logging to this part. ",
